                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/111.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>351. Department’s 282, July 12. Embassy doing everything possible to obtain
                    revision of War Department’s previous decision against Da Prato, but as yet no
                    reply received to its repeated and urgent requests for his release. Bringing
                    case to its attention again today</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy.</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
